First Lady Melania Trump and the White House Office of National Drug Control Policy (ONDCP) partnered to host an event called "Recovery at Work: Celebrating Connections" in recognition of National Alcohol and Drug Addiction Recovery Month. The event aimed to highlight the power of recovery tools and resources in the workplace, as well as the role of personal connection in achieving sobriety. The First Lady emphasized the importance of promoting healthy relationships and strong families through her Be Best initiative. National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow and Surgeon General Jerome Adams shared their personal stories of recovery, while First Lady of North Dakota Kathryn Burgum discussed her own journey. The participants also heard from individuals in recovery and the employers who support them. Mrs. Trump encouraged more employers to create work environments that prioritize the mental and physical well-being of employees and help eliminate stigma surrounding addiction. She emphasized the need for education and awareness to overcome drug abuse and addiction.